4.22 OECalcInternalCoord 
 
   
void OECalcInternalCoord(float *a, float *b, float *c, float *x,
                         float *z)
    
Given the Cartesian co-ordinates of the three reference atoms, in the
arrays a, b and c, convert the Cartesian coordinate specified by x, to
an internal coordinate in the buffer pointed to by z.

  

  
          
     
        
